					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In my next game, there are several sections that might use different colors, but where you can still move from one section to the other without a hard cut.<br /><br />For this, I'd like to do a color change like in &quot;Link's Awakening DX&quot;:<br /><!-- w --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YzEU19PUVuE&amp;t=13m19s">www.youtube.com/watch?v=YzEU19PUVuE&amp;t=13m19s</a><!-- w --><br /><br />Do you know of any automatic algorithm with which I can do the color change for an NES palette?<br /><br />I'm not talking about how to put this into PPU. I'm talking about a good way to transform one color into another one.<br /><br />Let's say I have color $05 in one screen and color $2A in the next. And I want to change one color into the other one with two steps in between. But I don't want to build a manual lookup array of every single color tranforming into every other color.<br /><br />Is there some automatism I can apply here?</div>

					
