					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I just don't know yet how I should decide which way to take when the other color is six steps away.</div><br />When the colors are five or six hues apart, you're cutting through the middle of the YUV/YIQ plane. This means you can go through the gray of roughly the same brightness. For example, for $22 to $28, use $22, $10, $28.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

